In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 25, 2011, as Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day. He acknowledges the sacrifices made by the men and women of the Armed Forces and the grief carried by their families. The president expresses gratitude and respect for Gold Star mothers and families, recognizing their support for each other and their communities. He honors the fallen heroes and promises to care for those left behind. The last Sunday in September is designated as Gold Star Mother's Day by Congress. The president calls upon government officials to display the flag and encourages the American people to do the same as a public expression of sympathy and respect for Gold Star Mothers and Families.